history.content:
You can use Options to change your section.

If you change to a full section, you will be moved to the first position on the waitlist for that section. This means that if no one drops from that section, you will not get into the class, yes. (You won't be "dropped", since you're not enrolled.)

children.subject: I don't see a reason to expect a higher or lower drop rate than other courses. So, 10% rule of thumb should still apply reasonably.
k, just curious because I have been monitoring very closely the last 3 days and have not noticed any movement at all which makes me very apprehensive.

I also wouldn't expect people to really be dropping at this time. Other than drops during Phases 1 / 2 / beginning of adjustment period when people are finalizing their schedules, most drops would be during the actual semester, as students get a feel of their courseloads.

So, if you weren't seeing any movement over the next 3 weeks, that would be more surprising.
